summary: BUICK CENTURY 1998 -[XXX] AND BUICK CENTURY 1996-[XXX].  BOTH VEHICLES ARE EXPERIENCING THE SAME PROBLEMS.  THE EXHAUST FUMES AND CARBON MONOXIDE GAS BLOWS INTO THE INTERIOR OF THE VEHICLE WHEN USING THE HEAT OR AIR CONDITIONER.  ALSO, THERE IS A SMELL OF ANTIFREEZE WHICH USUALLY OCCURS AFTER THE ENGINE IS WARM OR WHEN PARKED AFTER RUNNING.  BOTH OF THE VEHICLES WERE REPAIRED BUT THE PROBLEMS STILL EXIST.  *JG    INFORMATION REDACTED PURSUANT TO THE FREEDOM OF INFORMATION ACT (FOIA), 5 U.S.C. 552(B)(6).  *TR
